main event: Three rectangular-shaped objects were spotted in the sky over Zonguldak, Turkey on October 25, 1955. They disappeared and reappeared at intervals of 10-15 seconds, with a total duration of 45 minutes.
interesting points: The objects were observed by multiple sources over a significant period of time, adding credibility to the sighting.
The objects were seen over water at an estimated height of 5000-10000 ft, indicating that they were not close to the ground.
The objects exhibited a unique behavior of disappearing and reappearing at short intervals, suggesting advanced capabilities.
The presence of an aircraft at the location further supports the credibility of the sighting.
The duration of the observation, combined with the multiple witnesses, makes this an intriguing and well-documented event.
sighted object: three rectangular-shaped objects in the sky
